  <summary date="2017-12-11T19:08:31Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Fairness for Struggling Students Act of 2013

Amends federal bankruptcy law to make privately issued student loans dischargeable in bankruptcy. Under current law, student loans (whether issued privately or by a governmental unit) are dischargeable only if excepting the loans from dischargeability would impose undue hardship on the debtor and the debtor's dependents.</summary>
